The paper discusses a technique for faster retrieval of time series data using dynamic time warping (DTW) similarity measure. This involves the use of bounding techniques to avoid most DTW computations. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
